526":"–1526","–1548":"–1548","Bef 5 February 1517":"before 5 February 1517","1460":"1460","before 1516":"before 1516","after July 1516":"after July 1516","1524":"1524","after 1524":"after 1524","1455":"1455","after 1516":"after 1516","about 1526":"about 1526","1485":"1485","1517":"1517","1516":"1516","1548":"1548","1526":"1526","Glemsford, Suffolk, England":"Glemsford, Suffolk, England","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England","Glemsford, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Glemsford, Suffolk, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Isabelle","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   Isabel  , now in frequent use in the English-speaking world."],"variants":[{"name":"Isabel","meanings":["Originally a Spanish version of   Elizabeth  , which was coined by deletion of the first syllable and alteration of the final consonant sound to one that can normally end a word in Spanish. The name was imported into France in the early Middle Ages, and thence into England. It was a royal name, and its enduring popularity may have been enhanced by the fact that it was borne by a queen of England—  Isabella  (  1296–1358 ), daughter of  Philip IV  of France—even though she led a turbulent life and eventually had her husband,  Edward II , murdered."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":47,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Isabelle married John Strutt in 1485, in Glemsford, Suffolk, England. They were the parents of at least